parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of motive power, unable to accelerate, and failure of interior electrical components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and cannot accelerate above a certain speed
the low oil pressure warning light is illuminated
the engine does not shut off when turning off the vehicle
interior electrical components such as the radio and doors do not automatically lock
the push-to-start function does not operate as designed
the key fob battery needs to be replaced frequently
the dashboard lights go dark while driving
the battery dies unexpectedly
and the locks need to be unlocked manually.
